[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":211},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2021\u002F07\u002F04\u002Fhow-to-change-vscode-language\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2021\u002F07\u002F04\u002Fhow-to-change-vscode-language\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2021\u002F07\u002F04\u002Fhow-to-change-vscode-language\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2021\u002F07\u002F04\u002Fhow-to-change-vscode-language\u002F":187,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2021\u002F07\u002F04\u002Fhow-to-change-vscode-language\u002F":196},"\u002Fvscode\u002F20210704\u002F1752541725\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":170,"date":171,"description":172,"extension":173,"lang":174,"meta":175,"navigation":176,"path":177,"readingMinutes":178,"seo":179,"standalone":180,"stem":181,"tags":182,"tldr":184,"updated":171,"url":185,"__hash__":186},"content\u002Fen\u002FVSCode\u002Fhow-to-change-vscode-language.md","How to Change VSCode's Language in a Few Quick Steps","8144838073",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":162},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,34,37,43,46,52,55,61,64,70,78,84,87,93,96,100,103,106,112,115,119,122,128,131,136,139,145,149,152],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Quick note on how to switch VSCode's language. I'll walk through both macOS and Windows.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"macos","macOS",[17,25,26],{},"Open VSCode. I'll use switching to Traditional Chinese as the demo. The default is English:",[17,28,29],{},[30,31],"img",{"alt":32,"src":33},"VSCode default English","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FVSCode\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96_2021-07-04_11_44_27.png",[17,35,36],{},"Open Extensions and click in:",[17,38,39],{},[30,40],{"alt":41,"src":42},"Extensions","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FVSCode\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96_2021-07-04_11_45_31.png",[17,44,45],{},"In the \"Search Extensions in Marketplace\" box, type the English name of the language you want — e.g. Chinese:",[17,47,48],{},[30,49],{"alt":50,"src":51},"Search \"Chinese\"","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FVSCode\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96_2021-07-04_11_48_14.png",[17,53,54],{},"Or just search for Traditional (Simplified is for Simplified Chinese):",[17,56,57],{},[30,58],{"alt":59,"src":60},"Search \"Traditional\"","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FVSCode\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96_2021-07-04_11_49_25.png",[17,62,63],{},"Before installing, check the install count and star rating. I'd also recommend picking the Microsoft-published language pack:",[17,65,66],{},[30,67],{"alt":68,"src":69},"Ratings","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FVSCode\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96_2021-07-04_11_50_53.png",[17,71,72,73,77],{},"After installing, VSCode will tell you \"in order to use VS Code in Chinese Traditional, VS Code needs to restart.\" — basically restart it. You can click the Restart button at the bottom right, or fully quit VSCode (right-click the Dock icon and Quit, or ",[74,75,76],"code",{},"Cmd + Q","):",[17,79,80],{},[30,81],{"alt":82,"src":83},"Restart prompt","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FVSCode\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96_2021-07-04_11_51_06.png",[17,85,86],{},"After restart, you're in your new language:",[17,88,89],{},[30,90],{"alt":91,"src":92},"Traditional Chinese applied","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FVSCode\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96_2021-07-04_11_56_49.png",[17,94,95],{},"Same process for switching to any other language.",[12,97,99],{"id":98},"windows","Windows",[17,101,102],{},"The Windows process is basically identical to macOS, but for the sake of Windows users I'll screenshot the equivalent steps. Forgive me if I cut a few corners.",[17,104,105],{},"Open VSCode. Again, demoing with Traditional Chinese:",[17,107,108],{},[30,109],{"alt":110,"src":111},"VSCode default","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FVSCode\u002F2021-07-04_12-03-33.png",[17,113,114],{},"Open Extensions:",[17,116,117],{},[30,118],{"alt":41,"src":111},[17,120,121],{},"Search for the language English name, e.g. Chinese:",[17,123,124],{},[30,125],{"alt":126,"src":127},"Search Chinese","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FVSCode\u002F2021-07-04_12-05-04.png",[17,129,130],{},"Same rules apply — check install count and ratings, prefer the Microsoft official pack:",[17,132,133],{},[30,134],{"alt":68,"src":135},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FVSCode\u002F2021-07-04_12-05-09.png",[17,137,138],{},"After installing, restart VSCode and you're done:",[17,140,141],{},[30,142],{"alt":143,"src":144},"Localized","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FVSCode\u002F2021-07-04_13-27-07.png",[12,146,148],{"id":147},"common-gotchas","Common gotchas",[17,150,151],{},"One thing that occasionally goes wrong: the language pack fails to apply, usually after a VSCode update. Two fixes:",[153,154,155,159],"ul",{},[156,157,158],"li",{},"Fully restart VSCode. This works on macOS but not Windows.",[156,160,161],{},"Uninstall the language pack and reinstall it. This works on both OSes.",{"title":163,"searchDepth":164,"depth":164,"links":165},"",2,[166,167,168,169],{"id":14,"depth":164,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":164,"text":23},{"id":98,"depth":164,"text":99},{"id":147,"depth":164,"text":148},"VSCode","2021-07-04 11:34:50","A quick note on how to switch VSCode's language to another locale — walking through both macOS and Windows.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002Fhow-to-change-vscode-language","2",{"title":6,"description":172},false,"en\u002FVSCode\u002Fhow-to-change-vscode-language",[170,183],"Localization",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2021\u002F07\u002F04\u002Fhow-to-change-vscode-language\u002F","Z7JYVq1oyccx8STSC1Z2ON8AkTvbMkBJcQfKgnGx4NU",{"newer":188,"older":192},{"url":189,"title":190,"date":191},"\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2021\u002F07\u002F09\u002Fvscode-auto-fix-eslint-errors-on-save\u002F","Auto-fixing ESLint Errors in VSCode (on Save and on Format)","2021-07-09 09:41:16",{"url":193,"title":194,"date":195},"\u002Fen\u002Fgit\u002F2021\u002F06\u002F30\u002Fgithub-password-auth-brownout-fix\u002F","Fixing 'Password authentication is temporarily disabled as part of a brownout'","2021-06-30 17:23:37",[197,202,207],{"url":198,"title":199,"date":200,"readingMinutes":201},"\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2025\u002F04\u002F24\u002Fvscode-cannot-find-git-set-git-path\u002F","VSCode 'Can't Find Git, Install It or Use git.path' — How to Fix","2025-04-24 09:52:23","1",{"url":203,"title":204,"date":205,"readingMinutes":206},"\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2024\u002F09\u002F08\u002Fgithub-copilot-tips-and-tricks-deep-dive\u002F","GitHub Copilot Feels Awkward? You Might Just Not Know These Tricks","2024-09-08 13:06:00","5",{"url":208,"title":209,"date":210,"readingMinutes":201},"\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2023\u002F10\u002F26\u002Fvscode-vue-custom-component-syntax-highlight-fix\u002F","Vue Custom Components Lost Their Highlighting in VSCode — Here's the Fix","2023-10-26 11:03:07",1784011716097]